    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I have rebased this to account for #13025.\r\n\r\nBecause the new `WithMakeAnimation` method doesn't have the animation workaround, I had to change the way this PR works slightly, pulling out the `FrameEndTask` triggering into its own method that is ran directly on completion of the make animation, if the actor has one.  This avoids the one-tick delay that otherwise causes the visual glitch."
